tip_text: Explore different research labs early in your COS journey.
Join the HackPrinceton club, great for networking.
Take a creative writing workshop, even if you're not a major.
Office hours are your best friend for complex ELE courses.
Start your senior thesis proposal early!
Utilize the career services for internship opportunities in finance.
The history department has amazing faculty, connect with them!
Don't be afraid to take classes outside your comfort zone.
The writing center is a fantastic resource for all assignments.
Look into the integrated science curriculum, it's challenging but rewarding.
Princeton's alumni network is incredibly valuable, use it wisely.
Attend guest lectures! You never know what might inspire you.
